Vice President Joe Biden spoke with Cypriot President Nicos Anastasiades to discuss bilateral relations and various issues. They discussed the ongoing discussions on a comprehensive settlement for Cyprus, with the Vice President expressing strong support for a settlement that would reunify Cyprus as a bi-zonal, bi-communal federation with political equality. They also talked about the crisis in Ukraine, with the Vice President emphasizing the need to impose consequences on Russia if it continued its current actions and failed to support a ceasefire, peace talks, the release of hostages, border monitoring, and a halt to the transfer of weapons to separatists.